WEBVTT

1
00:00:29.520 --> 00:00:32.160
Yo, Sasaki.

2
00:00:32.610 --> 00:00:34.910
Hey, what's up?

3
00:00:35.770 --> 00:00:37.310
The heck, man?

4
00:00:37.310 --> 00:00:41.080
I looked all over for you 'cuz you weren't
in the smoking lounge downstairs.

5
00:00:41.590 --> 00:00:44.930
Oh, my bad. Did you need me for something?

6
00:00:53.970 --> 00:00:56.240
The chief wants to have 
a meeting in a few.

7
00:00:57.570 --> 00:00:58.350
Sheesh.

8
00:00:59.610 --> 00:01:04.870
Here we go with another pointless meeting 
that goes on and on and on and on and on.

9
00:01:05.540 --> 00:01:06.700
Now, now.

10
00:01:08.010 --> 00:01:09.740
Man...

11
00:01:15.270 --> 00:01:17.970
I just wanna go home already.

12
00:01:23.930 --> 00:01:25.660
I feel you.

13
00:05:24.820 --> 00:05:26.620
Thank you! Come again!

14
00:05:29.200 --> 00:05:30.570
Welcome!

15
00:05:33.070 --> 00:05:35.360
Do you have your loyalty point card?

16
00:05:35.360 --> 00:05:37.210
I do, yes.

17
00:05:37.800 --> 00:05:39.090
Thank you.

18
00:05:40.930 --> 00:05:42.910
Here's your card back.

19
00:05:49.340 --> 00:05:51.600
Would you like a bag?

20
00:05:52.230 --> 00:05:53.780
I'll take a three-yen one, please.

21
00:05:53.780 --> 00:05:57.730
That'll be 883 yen in total.

22
00:05:57.730 --> 00:05:58.730
Here.

23
00:06:06.690 --> 00:06:09.010
Here's your change and receipt.

24
00:06:10.180 --> 00:06:11.080
Thanks.

25
00:06:14.040 --> 00:06:15.720
Thank you! Come again!

26
00:06:23.020 --> 00:06:25.140
Yamada-san at register two...

27
00:06:26.010 --> 00:06:28.640
She's my post-work chill pill.

28
00:06:31.090 --> 00:06:32.520
That said...

29
00:06:33.520 --> 00:06:37.330
I've been going too often lately, 
even when I don't need anything.

30
00:06:37.330 --> 00:06:39.770
What a stupid waste of money.

31
00:06:40.270 --> 00:06:43.380
Maybe I should try offering it 
to Yamada-san as a gift.

32
00:06:43.740 --> 00:06:45.740
You never know. Might make her happy.

33
00:06:46.420 --> 00:06:49.090
Wow! Thank you so much!

34
00:06:52.840 --> 00:06:58.130
I sound like one of those delusional 
middle-aged criminals on the news.

35
00:06:59.270 --> 00:07:02.420
What is the meaning of this, Sasaki-kun?!

36
00:07:02.420 --> 00:07:06.680
Do you think "doing your rounds" 
just means going on a leisurely stroll?!

37
00:07:06.680 --> 00:07:10.730
I swear! It is unacceptable 
that you didn't let me know!

38
00:07:10.730 --> 00:07:12.310
I apologize, sir.

39
00:07:12.310 --> 00:07:15.940
You need to work on your 
communication, big-time!

40
00:07:15.940 --> 00:07:18.200
You're making me look bad 
as your manager—

41
00:07:18.200 --> 00:07:22.320
Sorry for interrupting, Chief, 
but Eda-san of Shikaku Inc.

42
00:07:22.680 --> 00:07:24.960
wants to know if the estimate is ready.

43
00:07:24.960 --> 00:07:28.200
Ack! Tell him I'll send it over tomorrow!

44
00:07:29.290 --> 00:07:31.770
We apologize for keeping you waiting!

45
00:07:31.770 --> 00:07:33.160
Yes, we'll send it over tomorrow!

46
00:07:33.160 --> 00:07:35.540
Of course! We're terribly sorry!

47
00:07:34.570 --> 00:07:36.580
We're having a meeting at 7 PM!

48
00:07:41.980 --> 00:07:44.660
That moronic boss of mine...

49
00:07:45.060 --> 00:07:47.280
It's bad enough that 
the meeting ran until midnight,

50
00:07:47.280 --> 00:07:49.550
but we didn't even decide on anything.

51
00:07:49.550 --> 00:07:50.590
I'll kill him...

52
00:07:51.410 --> 00:07:53.640
Or not. Just kidding.

53
00:07:53.640 --> 00:07:54.600
At times like these...

54
00:07:55.280 --> 00:07:56.690
There's no better time!

55
00:07:57.900 --> 00:07:59.780
Tonight, I go see Yamada-san!

56
00:08:01.180 --> 00:08:03.860
Here's your change.

57
00:08:04.370 --> 00:08:06.690
Thank you. Come again.

58
00:08:07.310 --> 00:08:08.450
Thank you.

59
00:08:11.650 --> 00:08:15.250
I guess Yamada-san's off. 
Or maybe she just finished already.

60
00:08:15.250 --> 00:08:17.960
Nothing's going my way today.

61
00:08:19.020 --> 00:08:22.310
I might need a little nicotine pick-me-up.

62
00:08:23.460 --> 00:08:25.460
Yikes. Look at that guy.

63
00:08:25.730 --> 00:08:27.950
What a nasty fellow.

64
00:08:35.970 --> 00:08:39.230
Wait, they don't have 
a smoking area either?

65
00:08:39.230 --> 00:08:40.890
You're kidding me.

66
00:08:40.890 --> 00:08:44.070
Are we smokers that ostracized these days?

67
00:08:44.070 --> 00:08:45.730
Hey, mister.

68
00:08:46.380 --> 00:08:48.510
Over here.

69
00:08:53.830 --> 00:08:56.740
You can light up over here.

70
00:08:57.010 --> 00:08:59.750
Whoa! Talk about tempting!

71
00:08:59.750 --> 00:09:03.730
Wait. Is this the back of the supermarket?

72
00:09:06.760 --> 00:09:09.590
Won't you get in trouble for letting 
an outsider use this place?

73
00:09:11.180 --> 00:09:14.890
Relax. Nobody knows who's in or out here.

74
00:09:15.810 --> 00:09:18.720
I guess I'll take you up on that, then.

75
00:09:18.720 --> 00:09:20.420
Sure. Go ahead.

76
00:09:34.530 --> 00:09:37.100
I have no idea what kind of look that is,

77
00:09:37.100 --> 00:09:39.040
but she's got quite 
the striking appearance.

78
00:09:39.730 --> 00:09:42.950
She looks the furthest thing 
from a supermarket employee.

79
00:09:45.910 --> 00:09:51.550
Um, miss? Which section do you work?

80
00:09:54.700 --> 00:09:57.180
C'mon, gimme a light.

81
00:09:57.180 --> 00:09:59.060
That's why I called you back here.

82
00:09:59.620 --> 00:10:01.390
Just say that, then!

83
00:10:01.390 --> 00:10:03.940
Sorry, let my intrusive thoughts win.

84
00:10:05.090 --> 00:10:07.700
Maybe don't do that to a guy you just met.

85
00:10:15.250 --> 00:10:19.530
You're the guy who always lines up 
at register two, aren't you?

86
00:10:22.650 --> 00:10:25.290
Huh, do I? Must be a coincidence.

87
00:10:26.110 --> 00:10:29.920
Coincidence? Even though you line up 
there when the others are free?

88
00:10:29.920 --> 00:10:31.670
Caught in 4K!

89
00:10:32.450 --> 00:10:34.680
Yamada-san's your favorite, then?

90
00:10:35.920 --> 00:10:38.980
She's messing with me on purpose!

91
00:10:39.940 --> 00:10:41.630
I get it.

92
00:10:41.630 --> 00:10:43.720
Gotta love Yamada-san, right?

93
00:10:44.810 --> 00:10:47.640
She's pretty and hella stacked,

94
00:10:47.640 --> 00:10:50.420
but you don't get the feeling she's taken.
It's like hitting the jackpot.

95
00:10:50.420 --> 00:10:51.940
You've got it all wrong!

96
00:10:51.940 --> 00:10:56.700
Sure, I may be a creepy guy who 
goes out of his way to line up for her,

97
00:10:57.040 --> 00:11:00.830
but that's just because 
seeing her at work lifts my spirits!

98
00:11:01.260 --> 00:11:03.850
That's the part that feels like 
hitting the jackpot!

99
00:11:08.040 --> 00:11:09.580
I-I'm sorry.

100
00:11:09.580 --> 00:11:11.340
I got too worked up there.

101
00:11:13.120 --> 00:11:14.780
Now I feel better.

102
00:11:15.470 --> 00:11:19.090
I was afraid she had another 
creepo shopper on her hands.

103
00:11:19.370 --> 00:11:23.110
Too many morons come here 
trying to get in her pants.

104
00:11:24.960 --> 00:11:27.930
But you're not one of them, huh?

105
00:11:30.180 --> 00:11:34.280
Try to keep it classy, Sasaki-san.

106
00:11:37.920 --> 00:11:41.500
I'd assumed she was the cocky type 
who mocked older men like me for fun,

107
00:11:41.500 --> 00:11:44.410
but she was actually just a nice girl 
who cares for her coworkers.

108
00:11:45.030 --> 00:11:46.090
Hey, uh...

109
00:11:47.910 --> 00:11:50.220
Your bill's ready to pay.

110
00:11:50.220 --> 00:11:52.420
Oh, sorry about that.

111
00:11:58.910 --> 00:12:00.680
Um, Sasaki-san.

112
00:12:00.680 --> 00:12:03.680
Huh? H-How do you know my name?

113
00:12:03.970 --> 00:12:07.580
Oh, I got it from your point card.

114
00:12:07.580 --> 00:12:08.330
Ah...

115
00:12:09.430 --> 00:12:11.060
Thank you. I appreciate it.

116
00:12:12.910 --> 00:12:16.770
I heard from Tayama-chan, 
and it really made me happy.

117
00:12:16.770 --> 00:12:17.490
Huh?

118
00:12:17.490 --> 00:12:20.510
She told me you're a fan of mine.

119
00:12:21.570 --> 00:12:23.610
You dropped this.

120
00:12:24.190 --> 00:12:25.900
Sorry about that.

121
00:12:27.980 --> 00:12:29.830
Thank you. Come again.

122
00:12:29.830 --> 00:12:33.110
Damn it, Tayama!

123
00:12:33.930 --> 00:12:35.880
Now that I know your name, 
you're going down!

124
00:12:36.570 --> 00:12:39.090
Heyo, it's Tayama.

125
00:12:45.190 --> 00:12:47.100
And come to the smoking area again,

126
00:12:47.610 --> 00:12:49.520
Sasaki-san.

127
00:12:49.520 --> 00:12:54.110
Wait, how did Tayama-san know my name?
